Overview

This is a simple console-based racing game developed in C using Dev-C++.
You control a racing car (@) that moves across three lanes and avoids obstacles (O).
The game features a unique colorful score system and a button-style Game Over screen.

Features

Simple gameplay: Move left or right to avoid obstacles.

Smooth animation: The car and obstacles move smoothly in the console.

Score system: Colorful, animated score bar updates as you survive.

Restart/quit buttons: Game Over screen shows clickable-looking buttons.

Single player: Fun and addictive gameplay.

Controls

Left Arrow (‚Üê): Move car to the left lane.

Right Arrow (‚Üí): Move car to the right lane.

R: Restart the game after Game Over.

Q: Quit the game after Game Over.

Gameplay

The car (@) moves in 3 lanes.

Obstacles (O) appear randomly in any lane.

Avoid obstacles until the step counter reaches the end.

Each successful pass increases the score by 1.

When the car collides with an obstacle, the Game Over screen appears.

Example Game Over Screen
  GAME OVER!
  Final Score: 12

+------------------+    +------------------+
|     RESTART      |    |      QUIT        |
+------------------+    +------------------+
   Press R                       Press Q

How to Run

Open Dev-C++ (or any Windows C compiler).

Copy the full code into a new project.

Compile and run.

Use arrow keys to move and avoid obstacles.

Code Structure

main() ‚Üí Starts the game loop and handles restarts.

playGame() ‚Üí Core game function, handles car movement, obstacle generation, and collision detection.

drawScoreBar() ‚Üí Draws a colorful score bar that changes color based on current score.

color(int c) ‚Üí Changes console text color for visual effects.

Dependencies

Windows OS (Uses windows.h for console colors and Sleep())

Dev-C++ (or any C compiler supporting Windows console)

Customization Ideas

Add multiple obstacles or faster speeds as score increases.

Include sound effects using Beep().

Change car character for variety (@, #, or ASCII art).

Add lives or power-ups.

